msgstr "2. The Second Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 14. Maṅgulitthisutta → maṅgulitthi ikkhanitthi (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn19.14:0.3"
msgid "14. Maṅgulitthisutta "
msgstr "14. A Fishwife "

# NOTE: BB has “ugly”, following comm. But mangula appears in MN 36, where the corresponding Sanskrit term in Lal 17 is madgura. This is a kind of fish or the caste of those who fish them. Fishwife seems to suit.
#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.260, sc1
msgctxt "sn19.14:1.1"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasaṃ itthiṃ duggandhaṃ maṅguliṃ vehāsaṃ gacchantiṃ. "
msgstr "“Just now, reverend, as I was descending from Vulture’s Peak Mountain I saw a stinking fishwife flying through the air. "

msgctxt "sn19.14:1.2"
msgid "Tamenaṃ gijjhāpi kākāpi kulalāpi anupatitvā anupatitvā vitacchenti virājenti. "
msgstr "Vultures, crows, and hawks kept chasing her, pecking, plucking, and hacking "

msgctxt "sn19.14:1.3"
msgid "Sā sudaṃ aṭṭassaraṃ karoti … pe … "
msgstr "as she screamed in pain. …” … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn19.14:1.4"
msgid "esā, bhikkhave, itthī imasmiṃyeva rājagahe ikkhaṇikā ahosi … pe …. "
msgstr "“That woman used to be a fortune-teller right here in Rājagaha. …” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn19.14:1.5"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

